> Blatt </PERSON> find the local district boundaries unconstitutional and order steps to promote integration. <PERSON> Blatt </PERSON> has ruled out busing as a possible remedy. <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> testified that about a third of the schools in the county can be identified as black, a third white and a third racially mixed. His guideline for determining a racially identifiable school is whether the black-white student ratio is more than 15 percent different from the black-white mix countywide. <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> said that of 35 schools that opened as identifiably white schools, 17 are still white. Of the 20 that opened as identifiably black schools, 17 are still black. The system of local district lines means `` you take away good solid educational choices from those who should be making the decisions,'' <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> said. `` The boundary becomes the decision.'' `` Educators should be making the decisions where children go to school, not boundaries,'' he added. He said adherence to the local boundaries has meant overcrowding in some county schools while others are n't being used to capacity.
