eyond it. <PERSON> Jafer </PERSON> <PERSON> Barazanchi </PERSON>, the regional governor, said a `` mass evacuation'' of <LOCATION> Darbandikhan </LOCATION>'s population was being considered. Mourners demanded revenge, not evacuation. About 10,000 people marched Monday behind 15 coffins draped in <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> flags, chanting slogans against <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s revolutionary patriarch. At the cemetery they shouted `` Death to <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>!'' and waved a banner reading: `` Fire more <PERSON> Al </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> missiles on the criminals in <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> in revenge for our people.'' <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> has given its long-range missiles the name <PERSON> Al </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON>, for a Shiite Moslem saint, and claims to have developed them itself. Western military analysts say the missiles are Soviet-made Scud-Bs with strap-on boosters enabling them to reach <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>, nearly 300 miles from the border.
