<HEAD>Iraq, Iran Unleash Air, Ground Assaults</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 8 grafs to UPDATE with Iraqi report of eight
missiles fired into Tehran and claims of plane and helicopter
downed. Picks up 6th graf pvs bgng: It said ...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ED BLANCHE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> shot missiles at each other's most heavily populated cities and pounded border towns with renewed intensity Monday after a weekend truce. Scores of civilians were killed and wounded. In a resumption of the `` war of the cities,'' <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> reported it fired eight surface-to-surface missiles into <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s capital of <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>, the last one at 11:27 p.m., and <ORGANIZATION> Iran </ORGANIZATION> said its forces shot two missiles at <LOCATION> Baghdad </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> capital. The Iraqis, declaring an all-out offensive on Iranian cities, also launched air raids on `` military and economic targets'' in Dezful, <LOCATION> Kermanshah </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Shushtar </PERSON> and three other border towns, scoring what it said were `` destructive hits.'' Iraqi communiques said the air raids were carried out in a 40-minute period, with all planes returning safely. <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> also claimed its helicopter gunships downed an Iranian helicopter. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, meanwhile, claimed its Revolutionary Guards and Iranian-backed Kurdish guerrillas have killed or wounded 1,900 Iraqis during ground assaults that began Sunday in the mountains of northeast <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Tehran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> reported <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> fired nine surface-to-surface missiles into Umm Qasr, an industrial town near <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>'s southern border with <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, and said anti-aircraft gunners shot down an Iraqi fighter-bomber in the northeastern battles. The official <ORGANIZATION> Iraqi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, monitored in <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION>, said the Iraqis fired eight long-range <PERSON> Al </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> missiles into <