/PERSON> pointed out that Orthodox women do shorten their skirts when the styles are shorter. In the 1960s, `` more religious women were walking around with skirts right by their knees.'' But as calf-length caught on, the shorter skirt became unacceptable. Now, she says, the women who shop at <LOCATION> Kutiel </LOCATION> _ including the manager _ could have stepped out of <LOCATION> Vogue </LOCATION>. `` OK, my leopard hat and bag do help,'' she said.
