<HEAD>BC-SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>FASHION: Mini Survey</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 The mini is not for the many, according to a survey published in a newsletter for marketers. The especially short, thigh-high miniskirt is appropriate only for `` the young, the skinny and the bold when they're at play,'' according to the Langer Report. Its findings were based on a study of women 15 to 64 years old, conducted in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> during November and December 1987. `` It is for a small minority of women, a minority of the time,'' said <PERSON> Judith </PERSON> <PERSON> Langer </PERSON>, publisher and co-editor of the report, which says the `` thigh-high micro-mini is seen by women as tacky _ worn to attract male attention, but not respect.'' <ORGANIZATION> Langer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> is a New York-based market research firm.
</TEXT>
