<FIRST>r f BC-S&amp;PChange     03-14 0377</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-S&amp;P Change,0390</SECOND>
<HEAD>Standard &amp; Poor's Changing its 500-Stock Index</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Poor </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it will restructure its widely followed index of 500 issues traded on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, effective April 6. S & amp; P's 500 Composite Stock Price Index will no longer contain a fixed number of industrial, utility, financial and transportation companies. The composite index currently includes four sector indices with a set number of stocks: 400 Industrials, 40 Utilities, 40 Financials and 20 Transportation companies. The investment research company said it will continue to calculate sector indices, but they will be referred to as the S & amp; P Industrial Index, the Utilities Index, the Financial Index and the Transportation Index. The composite index will still contain a total of 500 companies. Although this is the first structural change in the <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P 500 index since 1976, market analysts said it should n't make a significant difference for stock traders. The index, which represents more than $ 2 trillion in market value, is used as the basis for many index-linked investment funds. S & amp; P said the revamping is designed to respond to economic changes. The change `` reflects a major shift toward a more service-oriented <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> economy, illustrated by the increasing number of highly-capitalized companies in the financial services industry,'' said <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P Executive Vice President <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Andrialis </PERSON>. He said the change will allow <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P to be more flexible in choosing new companies for the index when openings occur and in switching companies between sectors as their businesses change. Under the current system, when a company is removed from the 500-share index, usually due to a merger or acquisition, it is replaced by another company from the same sector. Now, if a transportation company were dropped, for example, it could be replaced with an industrial, utility or financial company. S & amp; P also announced that effective April 6, <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Salomon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> will be transferred from its composite index to its financial index. <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION>, formerly <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Can </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, divested itself in recent years of its container business and has made several acquisitions in the financial services area _ including the investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Smith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Barney </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Harris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Upham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in 1987. <PERSON> Salomon </PERSON>, formerly <ORGANIZATION> Phibro </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, has shifted its main focus from commodities trading to financial services.
</TEXT>
