<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0325</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices marked time in quiet trading today as traders looked ahead to a potentially volatile week. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 1.49 to 2,036.47 by 2 p.m. on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by about 4 to 3 in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 619 up, 841 down and 439 unchanged. Analysts said traders were reluctant to take big positions in advance of the government's report Thursday on the nation's trade balance for January. The trade deficit narrowed in the last two months of 1987, but some analysts expect the January data to show a modest increase in the gap between exports and imports. This week's trade report will come just ahead of a quarterly `` triple witching hour'' involving a group of expiring options and futures on stock indexes. The past couple of witching hours have been relatively uneventful with the adoption of new procedures designed to spread out the impact of last-minute maneuvering by computer program traders. Nevertheless, analysts say uncertainty about how it will go this time has lent an added element of uncertainty to a marketplace still haunted by memories of the crash last fall. <ORGANIZATION> Grolier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> led the active list, up 8 -LRB- at 24. <ORGANIZATION> Hachette </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> made a $ 21-a-share offer to acquire the company. <PERSON> J.P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stevens </PERSON> climbed 5 \ to 61 The company agreed to be acquired for $ 61.50 a share by an investor group. <ORGANIZATION> Homestake </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mining </ORGANIZATION> fell 1 -LRB- to 15 -LRB-. <ORGANIZATION> Mesa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> L.P. </ORGANIZATION> withdrew a $ 20-a-share takeover bid that <ORGANIZATION> Homestake </ORGANIZATION> had opposed. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks lost .01 to 149.44. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up .61 at 296.70. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 87.53 million shares with two hours to go.
