<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreetClosing     03-14 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0178</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A flurry of buying just before the close enabled stock prices to post a gain in a quiet session today. Analysts said traders were reluctant to take big positions in advance of the government's report Thursday on the nation's trade balance for January. The trade deficit narrowed in the last two months of 1987, but some analysts expect the January data to show a modest increase in the gap between exports and imports. This week's trade report will come just ahead of a quarterly `` triple witching hour'' involving a group of expiring options and futures on stock indexes. The past couple of witching hours have been relatively uneventful with the adoption of new procedures designed to spread out the impact of last-minute maneuvering by computer program traders. Nevertheless, analysts say uncertainty about how it will go this time has lent an added element of uncertainty to a marketplace still haunted by memories of the crash last fall.
</TEXT>
